abstract: Tom Perez has the worst job in American politics, and he beat Pete Buttigieg to get it.

abstract: Former FBI Director James Comey acknowledged Sunday that a Justice Department  inspector general report  identified “real sloppiness" in the surveillance of a former Trump campaign aide and said he was wrong to have been “overconfident" about how the Russia investigation was handled.
snippet: Former FBI Director James Comey acknowledged Sunday that a Justice Department  inspector general report  identified “real sloppiness" in the surveillance of a former Trump campaign aide and said he was wrong to have been “overconfident" about how ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former FBI Director James Comey acknowledged Sunday that a Justice Department inspector general report identified “real sloppiness" in the surveillance of a former Trump campaign aide and said he was wrong to have been “overconfident" about how the Russia investigation was handled.
headline_main: Comey: 'Real Sloppiness' in Russia Probe but No Misconduct
headline_print_headline: Comey: 'Real Sloppiness' in Russia Probe but No Misconduct

abstract: The senior U.S. Senate Democrat called on Sunday for the Republican-led chamber to demand testimony from four current and former White House aides in a trial expected early next year on whether to remove President Donald Trump from office.
snippet: The senior U.S. Senate Democrat called on Sunday for the Republican-led chamber to demand testimony from four current and former White House aides in a trial expected early next year on whether to remove President Donald Trump from office.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The senior U.S. Senate Democrat called on Sunday for the Republican-led chamber to demand testimony from four current and former White House aides in a trial expected early next year on whether to remove President Donald Trump from office.
headline_main: Schumer Seeks Testimony From Mulvaney, Bolton in Expected Senate Trial of Trump
headline_print_headline: Schumer Seeks Testimony From Mulvaney, Bolton in Expected Senate Trial of Trump

abstract: The Army and Naval academies said they were looking into whether hand symbols by cadets and midshipmen at a football game on Saturday were related to hate groups.
snippet: The Army and Naval academies said they were looking into whether hand symbols by cadets and midshipmen at a football game on Saturday were related to hate groups.
lead_paragraph: United States military officials said they were investigating whether Army cadets and Navy midshipmen had flashed hand symbols associated with hate groups during a nationally televised pregame show before their football matchup on Saturday.

abstract: In the first nominating state, many Democrats feel a responsibility to identify a candidate who can win in states more diverse than their own.
snippet: In the first nominating state, many Democrats feel a responsibility to identify a candidate who can win in states more diverse than their own.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Iowa — They share awkward glances at events where nearly everyone looks like them. They take comfort in reminding one another that they propelled Barack Obama to the White House. They swear that their values and priorities are representative of more than a Corn Belt farm state.

abstract: Chinese Embassy officials trespassed onto a Virginia base that is home to Special Operations forces. Their expulsions added to tensions between Washington and Beijing.
snippet: Chinese Embassy officials trespassed onto a Virginia base that is home to Special Operations forces. Their expulsions added to tensions between Washington and Beijing.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The American government secretly expelled two Chinese Embassy officials this fall after they drove on to a sensitive military base in Virginia, according to people with knowledge of the episode. The expulsions appear to be the first of Chinese diplomats suspected of espionage in more than 30 years.
